<paragraph id="BE6311923721DB56BA0B654115729360" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<taxonomicName id="97C975516112532643CE810C0A974C85" authority="Spinola, 1841" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tillicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tillicera" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Tillicera</taxonomicName>
Spinola, 1841: 73; 
<bibRefCitation id="C6B9522A96A6A297000EA2920EF1B96E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2359.1.1" author="Gerstmeier, R" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="1 - 34" refId="B5" refString="Gerstmeier, R, Bernhard, N, 2010. Revision of the genus Tillicera Spinola, 1841 (Coleoptera: Cleridae, Clerinae). Zootaxa 2359 (1): 1 - 34, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2359.1.1" title="Revision of the genus Tillicera Spinola, 1841 (Coleoptera: Cleridae, Clerinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2359.1.1" volume="2359" year="2010">Gerstmeier and Bernhard 2010</bibRefCitation>
: 3; 
<bibRefCitation id="F34C1E283333C219AB100DBFA4EEBF29" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4193.3.4" author="Gerstmeier, R" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="517 - 540" refId="B6" refString="Gerstmeier, R, Stapel, J, 2016. A review of the Tillicera genus group with a revision of Plathanocera Schenkling (Coleoptera, Cleridae, Clerinae). Zootaxa 4193 (3): 517 - 540, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4193.3.4" title="A review of the Tillicera genus group with a revision of Plathanocera Schenkling (Coleoptera, Cleridae, Clerinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4193.3.4" volume="4193" year="2016">Gerstmeier and Stapel 2016</bibRefCitation>
: 539.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5A2F14A01A9B002029E60B1D0B062293" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="15FA4F8F1D9A5BD3E579587054BA3D77" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B16CE3D52F4CD53FA21E9446E5C29F08" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="3452320622D8C5DFC76D863A511B3589" authority="Spinola, 1841" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tillicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tillicera" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BDD6E94F9DC448CD1B3C6941EA1644A0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tillicera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="3B04C2F40C881317CE38F3A3820590C1" authority="Gorham, 1876" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Hemitrachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hemitrachys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0BA3E4BAA0793E22730F9C654AA4BB89" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Hemitrachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gorham but differs from it by the following characteristics (
<bibRefCitation id="5CD9E4DA466DFC29593EEADD6E34EAD1" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3710.1.5" author="Yang, GY" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="72 - 80" refId="B22" refString="Yang, GY, Yang, XK, 2013. Revision of the genus Hemitrachys Gorham, with discovery of a second species (Coleoptera: Cleridae: Clerinae). Zootaxa 3710 (1): 72 - 80, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3710.1.5" title="Revision of the genus Hemitrachys Gorham, with discovery of a second species (Coleoptera: Cleridae: Clerinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3710.1.5" volume="3710" year="2013">Yang and Yang 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="312E9C626B93B986DE975D0F78CD860B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4193.3.4" author="Gerstmeier, R" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="517 - 540" refId="B6" refString="Gerstmeier, R, Stapel, J, 2016. A review of the Tillicera genus group with a revision of Plathanocera Schenkling (Coleoptera, Cleridae, Clerinae). Zootaxa 4193 (3): 517 - 540, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4193.3.4" title="A review of the Tillicera genus group with a revision of Plathanocera Schenkling (Coleoptera, Cleridae, Clerinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4193.3.4" volume="4193" year="2016">Gerstmeier and Stapel 2016</bibRefCitation>
): antennomeres V-XI not clubbed; elytral length to width ratio 2.01-2.37; pulvillar formula 4-4-2, 4-4-3 or 4-4-4 (
<taxonomicName id="94D2845CF7155D6473569809C525174F" authority="Gorham, 1876" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Hemitrachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hemitrachys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E2400017B8B822A046316281C2A3CE1B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Hemitrachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: antennomeres V-XI clubbed; elytral length to width ratio 1.58-1.80; pulvillar formula 4-2-2).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="70C06C22FE57559C4582A71C74E82E1A" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="EB1E9A68CFA4513F83B564744251979A" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3EB5CAD3E6E702873AF7A625258F6158" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
In male and female adults of 
<taxonomicName id="AC6DF27E9C30566CE4513910F989B440" baseAuthorityName="Gebler" baseAuthorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Thanasimus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thanasimus substriatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="substriatus">
<emphasis id="D497A255DA7AEA22B8B476D2798C7FA2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Thanasimus substriatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sensilla basiconica were distributed in clusters that formed a line along the posterior border from the fifth to the eighth antennomere (
<bibRefCitation id="B8247C8F98B5917F2A53618BD01726CF" DOI="https://doi.org/10.18474/JES20-70" author="Zhang, J" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Entomological Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="441 - 455" refId="B24" refString="Zhang, J, Cheng, B, Fu, L, Sun, S, 2021. Morphology and Distribution of Antennal Sensilla of the Predatory Clerid Beetle, Thanasimus substriatus (Coleoptera: Cleridae). Journal of Entomological Science 56 (3): 441 - 455, DOI: https://doi.org/10.18474/JES20-70" title="Morphology and Distribution of Antennal Sensilla of the Predatory Clerid Beetle, Thanasimus substriatus (Coleoptera: Cleridae)." url="https://doi.org/10.18474/JES20-70" volume="56" year="2021">Zhang et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
). The area of the apical margin of antennae in ventral view, which is vested with sensilla basiconica, was discovered in 
<taxonomicName id="E2731556F1CF93FFF7DCB7428FEF584A" authority="Spinola, 1841" authorityName="Gerstmeier &amp; Bernhard" authorityYear="2010" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tillicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tillicera callosa" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="callosa">
<emphasis id="6331E378588876BDB2DC831B849E0F8D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tillicera callosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="12B663229F40F62EC485014120487641" authority="Spinola, 1841" authorityName="Murakami &amp; Gerstmeier &amp; Sakai" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tillicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tillicera fortis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortis">
<emphasis id="A36E15F4A216E5FFBCF5F00B05E0E021" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tillicera fortis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., 
<taxonomicName id="B2BA7AAEF3F712E5B187D2124AE88E7F" authority="Spinola, 1841" authorityName="Murakami &amp; Gerstmeier &amp; Sakai" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tillicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tillicera spinosa" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis id="666E460BDF368336740A3351AE4A2EB9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tillicera spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., and 
<taxonomicName id="6C4286164D425C59E0A5789CBF038E98" authority="Gorham, 1876" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Hemitrachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hemitrachys tubericollis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tubericollis">
<emphasis id="D4EA0C689B36D4E679C51BEF6083B936" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Hemitrachys tubericollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Yang &amp; Yang, 2013 for the first time (Figs 
<figureCitation id="F4868AA2C4AC3DF763B36C7C42564C28" captionStart="Figures 28–31" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 28 - 31. Antennae of Tillicera spp. (28 dorsal view 29 - 31 ventral view) 28 male antennomere XI of T. spinosa sp. nov. 29 female antennomere X of T. spinosa sp. nov. 30 female antennomeres VII-IX of T. spinosa sp. nov. 31 male antennomeres IV and V of T. callosa. Abbreviations: P pit-like sensillum SB an area of sensilla basiconica." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80097.figures28-31" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672268" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">29-31</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="48C80AC1E4F11AE77E50411DEF74363C" captionStart="Figures 32–35" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 32 - 35. Hemitrachys tubericollis 32, 33 habitus in dorsal (32) and ventral (33) views 34 male antennomeres IX-XI in ventral view 35 male antennomeres V-VIII in ventral view. Abbreviations: SB an area of sensilla basiconica." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80097.figures32-35" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672269" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">34</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B61E41F1776266C9928768BC07915285" captionStart="Figures 32–35" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 32 - 35. Hemitrachys tubericollis 32, 33 habitus in dorsal (32) and ventral (33) views 34 male antennomeres IX-XI in ventral view 35 male antennomeres V-VIII in ventral view. Abbreviations: SB an area of sensilla basiconica." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.80097.figures32-35" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672269" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">35</figureCitation>
). The genus 
<taxonomicName id="3E544C977CC3EFA4F7DE3818EF22A957" authority="Spinola, 1841" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tillicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tillicera" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5CD8213B561824129281622EDB890304" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tillicera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is included in the 
<taxonomicName id="B58BE66C03F5B06D5A20993E1CDD149B" authority="Spinola, 1841" authorityName="Spinola" authorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tillicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tillicera" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="99DF4C740649DCBEB47AF4BD9926ED3C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tillicera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus group with 
<taxonomicName id="83048DA1CF4D82D10599D8B4EE4A6E75" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Apopempsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Apopempsis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D4D0628323BD439A9ED58E123C34D51D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Apopempsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="EDA5B942E62AECC992F6AAC299BD2352" authorityName="Quedenfeldt" authorityYear="1885" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Cardiostichus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cardiostichus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5C139996ED6DCFD9E475F08EF8B7D5EA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Cardiostichus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6BE921E11D353FAA7B35212A6C25C3D6" authority="Gorham, 1876" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Hemitrachys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hemitrachys" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5ACCE9B5B5C4FDD19CD7C0FC007FAEBC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Hemitrachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3B567C9765B9A07A56B660FAA2503DAB" authorityName="Klug" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Placocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Placocerus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6B5C956A9ABA9F90418B5A17BB911DF4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Placocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="A93AC98A65BA98442595B12253DAE43E" authority="Schenkling, 1902" authorityName="Schenkling" authorityYear="1902" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Plathanocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plathanocera" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="27313BF2446F3353D3F698262DE9C2EC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Plathanocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="7C80A0B6CBBDE9E14741E86A7E7002D3" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4193.3.4" author="Gerstmeier, R" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="517 - 540" refId="B6" refString="Gerstmeier, R, Stapel, J, 2016. A review of the Tillicera genus group with a revision of Plathanocera Schenkling (Coleoptera, Cleridae, Clerinae). Zootaxa 4193 (3): 517 - 540, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4193.3.4" title="A review of the Tillicera genus group with a revision of Plathanocera Schenkling (Coleoptera, Cleridae, Clerinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4193.3.4" volume="4193" year="2016">Gerstmeier and Stapel 2016</bibRefCitation>
); the monophyly of the genus group, however, is questioned by 
<bibRefCitation id="11F3BF86E50DCA22E614A741BA76362F" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3161/00034541ANZ2021.71.4.003" author="Bartlett, JS" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici (Warszawa)" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="737 - 766" refId="B1" refString="Bartlett, JS, 2021. A preliminary suprageneric classification for Clerinae (Coleoptera: Cleridae) based on molecular and morphological evidence, including a review of tegminal terminology. Annales Zoologici (Warszawa) 71 (4): 737 - 766, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3161/00034541ANZ2021.71.4.003" title="A preliminary suprageneric classification for Clerinae (Coleoptera: Cleridae) based on molecular and morphological evidence, including a review of tegminal terminology." url="https://doi.org/10.3161/00034541ANZ2021.71.4.003" volume="71" year="2021">Bartlett (2021)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D0D6841064A7AAF77E7C5F51BEDFB025" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
In the first 
<normalizedToken id="47B51256B57DC660597B477181A355BB" originalValue="author’s">author's</normalizedToken>
observations, this remarkable antennal structure is also seen in two other genera, 
<taxonomicName id="6279C79F6BE89829A800756EB472EB4F" authority="Geoffroy, 1762" authorityName="Geoffroy" authorityYear="1762" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Clerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Clerus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D0B85539F2910A200CB9BD59DF4B64ED" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Clerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Geoffroy, 1762 and 
<taxonomicName id="45D69CE897CE23624E4BD0FBCDA66E66" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Omadius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Omadius" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CCC82BDE3806DA709B1595E73BEEC999" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Omadius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Laporte, 1838, which are included into the subtribe 
<taxonomicName id="1E8DCB140A972B95DB540B620D9AC6CC" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" genus="Clerina" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="genus">Clerina</taxonomicName>
Latreille, 1802 (see 
<bibRefCitation id="1EC8FDA02BBF2E814A5597685E21752B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3161/00034541ANZ2021.71.4.003" author="Bartlett, JS" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici (Warszawa)" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="737 - 766" refId="B1" refString="Bartlett, JS, 2021. A preliminary suprageneric classification for Clerinae (Coleoptera: Cleridae) based on molecular and morphological evidence, including a review of tegminal terminology. Annales Zoologici (Warszawa) 71 (4): 737 - 766, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3161/00034541ANZ2021.71.4.003" title="A preliminary suprageneric classification for Clerinae (Coleoptera: Cleridae) based on molecular and morphological evidence, including a review of tegminal terminology." url="https://doi.org/10.3161/00034541ANZ2021.71.4.003" volume="71" year="2021">Bartlett 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Further investigation is required to clarify the intergeneric relationships.
</paragraph>
